    &quot;They named a horse that's part arabian Hercules?&quot;<br>
~She shook her head and walked out to the pasture, still chuckling. When she got there, she hopped the fence easily and walked to the middle, looking around at the handful of mares and the one stallion in the middle. Smiling to herself, she closed her eyes and called on her gift, reaching out to the mares' minds gently. Within minutes, she had gotten the harem to come to her. Various noses were thrust into her hands and back, trying to familiarize themselves with the scent of the one who had talked to them in their own language. Robin looked up, not breaking contact with the mares, and watched as Hercules stood neither close nor far from the harem of females. She sighed and nodded to herself. This one is gonna take some work, she thought.~ <p>            ~Robin~
~Credendo Vides~
